## 4) Practitioner-tested controls that improve output

### A) Force specificity
```text
Each paragraph must include one detail that is unique to this exact scene and would not fit another story.
```

### B) Enforce subtext
```text
Characters should avoid naming their core desire directly; reveal motive through interruption, misdirection, and loaded word choice.
```

### C) Manage pacing ratios
```text
Allocate word budget: 20% setup, 60% confrontation, 20% consequence.
```

### D) Prevent purple prose
```text
If any paragraph contains more than one figurative image, simplify to the strongest single image.
```

### E) Keep emotional writing concrete
```text
Replace abstract emotion labels with observable physical behavior and choices.
```

