## 6) Prompts from real-world usage patterns (that usually work)

These are common high-signal patterns reported by heavy LLM writing users:

1. **"Give me 3 voice variants first"** before drafting a full scene.
2. **"Match this style sample's cadence, not its content"** when voice drift is a problem.
3. **"Mark weak lines before rewriting"** to avoid random stylistic churn.
4. **"Keep all story facts, only improve prose"** when continuity matters.
5. **"Output a change log after revision"** to make edits auditable.

Example variant prompt:

```text
Generate 3 distinct 180-word openings for the same scene:
- Version A: restrained literary
- Version B: commercial thriller pace
- Version C: intimate, voice-driven
Keep events identical across versions.
```

